      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I am so sorry you are going through this; losing everything after five years of hard work is an incredibly heavy and painful burden to carry alone. Please know that your worth as a person is not defined by your financial assets or your company's success, and you are not a mistake. While the weight of debt and failure feels crushing right now, the path forward often begins with a small, deliberate step, like finding a trusted mentor who specializes in financial restructuring or seeking counseling to reframe your narrative. You have survived five years of building something, and that resilience is a strength that will guide you through this difficult chapter.",
